Class CefListValue

class CefListValue
extends CefBase

Class representing a list value. Can be used on any process and thread.

SetBinary

public virtual bool SetBinary( int index, CefRefPtr< CefBinaryValue > value )= 0;
Sets the value at the specified index as type binary. Returns true if the value was set successfully. After calling this method the |value| object will no longer be valid. If |value| is currently owned by another object then the value will be copied and the |value| reference will not change. Otherwise, ownership will be transferred to this object and the |value| reference will be invalidated.
